summary: The document is identified as a form within the JFK assassination system, detailing agency specifics, document details, and subjects involved, including references to military service and hostile intelligence. It mentions individuals such as Richard C. Nagell and Victor L. Trinkala. Originally classified as confidential, the document was regraded to unclassified in 1994.
key_findings: Document is part of the JFK ASSASSINATION SYSTEM IDENTIFICATION FORM.
References INSCOM/CSF agency and a specific record number.
Mentions individuals Richard C. Nagell and Victor L. Trinkala in relation to military service and hostile intelligence.
Originally classified as CONFIDENTIAL, regraded to UNCLASSIFIED on June 1, 1994.
Includes terms like 'CONSCIENTIOUS OBJECTOR' and 'CANCELLATION OF ORDERS'.
